notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Pentatuech, Hafṭarot and Psalms, with vowel-points and accents, masorah magna and parva, followed by a calendar in Persian.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 18 20; written lines: 18 20; Uniform layout. Number of columns on each page varies from 18 to 20. Incomplete at the beginning. Some folios were added later (folios 7-27, 34, 59, 66). Ruling is visible. Parallel Hebrew foliation. Catchword on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental (Persian) semi-cursive script, punctuated. Shemu᾿el ben Aharon ben Yosef: inscribed with his name in the colophon, 1794 [1483] (361r-361v).

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Pentateuch, Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental Ms. 2451.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolf Neubauer (b. 1832, d. 1907), Hebrew scholar born in Hungary: purchased by the British Museum from him on 24 June 1882: inscribed ([380v]).
